description: For sale: $863,390. Gorham Communities presents our Caden Model in the Royal Club Lake Elmo. Wonderful luxury villa floorplan for those seeking main level living and professional yard care. Soaring 11' ceilings, gourmet kitchen with granite tops and large walk-in prep kitchen pantry. Tiled walk-in master shower, heated bath floor, sep soaking tub. Bath links nicely to owners walk-in closet and laundry. 2 fireplaces, custom enameled and stained alder cabinets. Relax in your huge 14x18 sceened porch set against the trees. Light and bright lookout lower level includes a large bar area for entertaining and loads of storage throughout! 96% efficient Trane furnace, Andersen Windows, James Hardi ColorPlus siding, concrete driveway,  heated 3 car garage with floor drains, and epoxy floor finish with 2' added depth! With all the quality standards that Gorham promises for life long enjoyment, don't miss this opportunity to call the Royal Club home!

For sale: $500,733. Welcome to our Taylor floorplan in the beautiful Lake Ridge Crossing neighborhood. You will be near Lake Elmo Park Reserve for outdoor activities all year round as well as Woodbury for plenty of shopping and restaurant options to choose from. This 4-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom home has 2,374 square feet on a look-out homesite. The welcoming front porch, James Hardie® siding, and stone accents all add to the curb appeal along with the gorgeous landscaping. The added irrigation will keep your grass looking healthy and green each summer. The south-facing backyard allows natural light to flood the living spaces in this gorgeous two-story, single-family home. The expanded 3-car garage provides space for additional storage, a workshop, or kids' play equipment. The open and airy kitchen is a desired feature with an oversized center island featuring striking and modern navy cabinetry. The rest of the kitchen has white cabinetry with a gas stainless steel cooktop, decorative hood, dishwasher, wall oven/microwave, French door refrigerator, and large corner pantry. Upgraded quartz countertops are a highlight throughout the kitchen and bathrooms. Warm-toned luxury vinyl plank flooring covers the main level. The family room fireplace has a stone surround that makes its way half-way up the wall, capped with a gorgeous mantel. The owner's suite is appointed with double sinks, a full tile shower, and a window for natural light.  Schedule a personal tour today to call this home ...

For sale: $382,990. If you're looking for single level living, the Cedarwood is the perfect floor plan for you! This beautiful home from the Hans Hagen Villa Collection includes two spacious bedrooms, two full bathrooms, and a den. Plus, you'll be able to leave the yardwork behind and enjoy a lock-and-leave lifestyle in this association-maintained community. Step into the Cedarwood's spacious foyer and you'll be greeted by the light-filled den along with the secondary bedroom and bathroom, creating the perfect space for guests. Towards the back of the home, the kitchen is centrally located and open to the dining area and family room, keeping you connected at all times. Just beyond the dining area is an optional morning room, a favorite place for morning coffee, or an additional entertaining space. Just off the family room is the private owner's suite, a spacious retreat with optional ceiling soffits for a more dramatic feel. The owner's suite includes a large walk-in closet and private bathroom with a shower and double-vanities, plus options for a bathtub or walk-in shower. Call today to learn more about building the Cedarwood plan!

For sale: $540,890. This beautiful home offers main-level living at its best with three bedrooms, laundry room, and two bathrooms on the main floor. This one-level floorplan, the Kaiden, has plenty of curb appeal with a beautiful exterior and includes a convenient three-car garage.  The open-concept main living spaces of this home will help when entertaining or just enjoying family conversation as each room blends seamlessly into the next. Once entering the spacious foyer and heading towards the back of this home you'll stop to admire the stunning kitchen, which includes upgraded stainless steel appliances and a gas stove with a fan hood vented to the exterior. description:
Recently sold: $438,500. We have a light filled, Craftsman styled open floor plan home in the award winning open space community, Fields of St. Croix.  A welcoming front porch offers connection to the beautifully landscaped park surroundings.  The maple woodwork, cabinets, and flooring are custom, high end, and architecturally detailed.  A large entry leads to an open concept living room, kitchen, dining area, and sitting room. The main floor master bedroom has a walk in closet, large bathroom with a jetted tub, separate fully tiled shower, and double sinks.  The main floor laundry room with closet opens to an attached garage.  The finished lower lookout level has 2 bedrooms, a 3/4 bath, and large family room plus an ample unfinished storage area.  There is a dual thermostat system in the house and air exchanger system. The carpeting throughout the home, furnace, air conditioning, and air exchange system are 1 year old.
Our home is on a cul de sac quiet street of six homes with mature trees and plants directly across the street.  We have a restored historic barn at the end of the street which is available for homeowners to use free.  At the barn is access Goetschel Lake with a 1 mile paved path around it.  We have a playground 1 block from the house and several interconnected biking paths.   Our home was built by Senn and Youngdahl using quality materials inside and out.

description: Recently sold: $300,000. Built on a private 1-acre lot in the beautiful Demontreville Highlands neighborhood, close to the popular Tri-Lakes area, this phenomenal home was tastefully remodeled in 2012 and offers ample living and entertaining space.  As you enter, a two-story foyer presents a wow factor with its elegant chandelier and dramatic staircase leading to a catwalk above that overlooks the great room straight ahead.  Offering that extra needed space for hosting family and friends is a formal dining room on the left and living room on the right with a wet bar and French doors leading to a quaint office space.  The great room then showcases an impressive floor-to-ceiling, stone surround fireplace, plush carpet inlay, and walls of windows, allowing serene views of the treed backyard and loads of daylight to pour in.  From here, the open floor plan runs into the exquisite kitchen and informal dining space that lends access to a huge wrap around deck, running all the way from the laundry room on one end to the office on the other, while a private balcony deck above sits off the master suite.  This palatial space is a retreat with its luxurious bath remodeled with a tile surround jetted shower and whirlpool tub and gorgeous double vanities.  Three additional bedrooms and a full en suite, walk-thru bath are conveniently located on the upper level, while a mother-in-law suite can be found in the expansive walkout lower level.  With private access, your guests or family can feel at home in their own living quarter with a kitchen, remodeled ¾ bath, family room with brick surround fireplace, bedroom and flex room.  Multiple walkouts also lead to the sweeping, fenced-in backyard adorned with generous landscaping and mature trees.  This classic two-story home offers all the comfort and elegance one could ask for.

description: Recently sold: $615,000. Built on a large 2.6 acre lot in a prime location, this classic home was made to entertain and raise a growing family.  Upon entrance, you?ll be greeted with a bright and open two-story foyer and large doorways with beautiful transom windows to the formal living and dining rooms on either side.  Walk down a hallway, where the oak hardwood flooring runs into the open floor plan of the great room and kitchen.  Large windows in the great room allow for plenty of daylight and a gas fireplace with oak mantle and surround is the focal point.  In the casual dining area, a patio door amid two bay windows leads out to a deck offering private views of the beautifully landscaped backyard and pool below.  Appreciate updated light fixtures, knobs and hinges throughout the home, along with a gorgeous selection of granite for the kitchen countertops and large center island.  Oak cabinets offer more than enough storage space, and stainless steel appliances add to the overall fresh look and feel.  From the kitchen, there is access to the formal dining room, as well as the mudroom, laundry room and updated powder room off the garage entrance.  A solid oak spindle railing leads you to the spacious upper level landing that makes traffic and moving furniture a breeze.  The master suite is big and open, with a separate sitting area you can relax in and an updated en suite that offers a beautiful granite counter on the double vanity, tile surround shower with a decorative inlay and glass doors, whirlpool tub, in-floor heat and access to a large walk-in closet.  Two more bedrooms share a Jack & Jill bath, also impressively updated with granite, in-floor heat and another tile surround shower with glass doors, and an additional full bath services the fourth bedroom.  And no need to worry about room for storage, as there is a plethora of closet space throughout this level.  Make your way down the stairs to the lower level that leads you to a walkout with direct access to the pool and huge backyard or to the family room that features a striking floor-to-ceiling stone surround fireplace.  In addition to the numerous living spaces in this home, a recreation room with wet bar is great for entertaining, and a fifth bedroom and bath are perfect for guests.  Functional and conveniently located, this home is sure to please for many years to come.
